Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.logic

Interface Proposition

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<Logical>, Expression, Logical, Serializable, Simplifiable, Typed
All Known Subinterfaces:
Atom
All Known Implementing Classes:
Assignment, Clause, Comparison, Conjunction, Disjunction, Effect, False, Negation, Precondition, Quantified, True, TypeConstraint
public interface Proposition extends Expression
A proposition is a logical expression of type boolean. This interface implements some functionality that all Boolean expressions share, but Boolean expressions do not need to implement this interface.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • toValued

      default Conditional<Disjunction<Clause<Precondition>>> toValued()
      Description copied from interface: Expression
      Returns a conditional expression whose conditions are in disjunctive normal form and whose branches are valued expressions. This method is used to simplify expressions by converting anything which is not valued into valued expressions and moving any conditionals outside of the expression. If the expression is already valued, the conditional returned should have no conditions and a single branch that is this expression.
      Specified by:
      toValued in interface Expression
      Returns:
      a conditional with conditions in disjunctive normal form and branches that are valued expressions
